# ============================================================================
# NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS
# ============================================================================
#
# This .gitignore covers:
# - Frontend: Next.js, Node.js, npm/yarn
# - Backend: Flask, Python, pip/venv
# - Development: VS Code, PyCharm, Sublime, Vim, etc.
# - Deployment: Vercel, AWS, Docker
# - OS: macOS, Windows, Linux
# - Security: .env files, SSL certs, API keys
#
# IMPORTANT FILES TO KEEP TRACK OF:
# ✓ .env.sample (template for .env - COMMIT THIS)
# ✓ .env.example (template for .env - COMMIT THIS)
# ✗ .env (actual secrets - NEVER COMMIT)
# ✗ .env.local (actual secrets - NEVER COMMIT)
#
# TO ADD EXCEPTIONS:
# If you need to commit a file that matches a pattern above, use:
# !path/to/specific/file
#
# Example:
# !frontend/public/sample.env
#
# ============================================================================

# END OF .gitignore
